oc:kn_064a8559 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any interactive command" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Determine if interaction needs AskUserQuestion or simple arguments. 2. Design questions with clear labels and trade-off descriptions. 3. Build conditional flows that adapt based on earlier answers. 4. Validate responses and handle errors. 5. Confirm final configuration before executing changes." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_1455b054 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring multiSelect parameter" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never use multiSelect: true for mutually exclusive choices like database engine or authentication method selection." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mutually exclusive options should enforce single selection to prevent invalid configurations" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_2f9e7185 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing question options" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Option labels should be 1-5 words, specific and descriptive, with no jargon without context. Descriptions should explain what the option means, mention key benefits or trade-offs, and be 1-2 sentences." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Clear option design helps users make informed decisions quickly" .

oc:kn_3e05aeb2 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing multi-stage interactive workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Design question flows that build on previous answers: ask broad questions first, then conditionally ask detailed follow-ups. Use progressive disclosure — start simple, get detailed only as needed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Conditional flows reduce cognitive load by only showing relevant options" .

oc:kn_49daef8d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After receiving AskUserQuestion responses" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always validate AskUserQuestion responses. If answers are empty or invalid, show alternative approach and allow retry or manual configuration." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Interactive tools can fail or return unexpected data; graceful fallback maintains user trust" .

oc:kn_58471cab a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before running interactive commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify AskUserQuestion is listed in allowed-tools in frontmatter, question format is correct, and options array has 2-4 items before executing interactive commands." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Missing tool permissions or malformed questions cause silent failures" .

oc:kn_95ab10ef a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding between AskUserQuestion and command arguments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not use AskUserQuestion for simple values (file paths, numbers, names), known inputs the user already has, scriptable workflows, or fast invocations where prompting would slow things down. Use command arguments instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Interactive prompts for simple inputs add unnecessary friction and break automation workflows" ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_ea5f561a a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing command interactivity" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use AskUserQuestion for multiple choice decisions needing explanations, complex options requiring context, multi-select scenarios, preference gathering, and interactive workflows that adapt based on answers." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These scenarios benefit from structured choice presentation with trade-off explanations" .

oc:kn_f4f7f3dd a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing AskUserQuestion calls" ;
    oc:directiveContent "AskUserQuestion options must be 2-4 choices per question, with 1-4 questions per tool call. Headers must be max 12 characters." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Exceeding these limits overwhelms users and degrades the interactive experience" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

